 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\n",
    "   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n",
    "   \"language\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python3\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"version\": \"3.11.0\"\n",
    "  }\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Wine Quality Classification\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Classification Project 23 of 100** — Predict wine quality from physicochemical properties.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"EDA -> preprocessing -> baseline -> LazyPredict -> FLAML -> top-3 evaluation.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 2. Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Predict wine quality (score 3-9, binned to Low/Medium/High) from 11 physicochemical features. Uses the combined red and white wine datasets from UCI. This is a **medium** difficulty classification task due to class overlap.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 3. Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Ordinal target binned into 3 classes\\n\", \"2. All-numeric features (physicochemical tests)\\n\", \"3. Class imbalance (most wines are medium quality)\\n\", \"4. Feature correlation analysis\\n\", \"5. LazyPredict and FLAML benchmarking\\n\", \"6. Understanding that wine quality has significant class overlap\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 4. Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> Given 11 physicochemical properties (acidity, sugar, pH, alcohol, etc.), classify wine quality as Low (3-5), Medium (6), or High (7-9).\\n\", \"\\n\", \"3-class classification. Macro-F1 is primary metric.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 5. Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Stakeholder | Impact |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| Winemakers | Quality control optimization |\\n\", \"| Sommeliers | Objective quality assessment |\\n\", \"| Supply chain | Pricing and sorting |\\n\", \"| ML learners | Ordinal target, class overlap |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 6. Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| Source | UCI / Kaggle |\\n\", \"| Kaggle slug | uciml/red-wine-quality-cortez-et-al-2009 |\\n\", \"| Rows | ~6,497 (combined red + white) |\\n\", \"| Features | 11 numeric + 1 color indicator |\\n\", \"| Target | quality (3-9, binned to 3 classes) |\\n\", \"| Balance | Heavily medium-skewed |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 7. Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- UCI ML Repository — Cortez et al., 2009\\n\", \"- Kaggle: uciml/red-wine-quality-cortez-et-al-2009\\n\", \"- License: CC BY 4.0\\n\", \"- We use the red wine dataset; white wine can be added.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 8. Environment Setup\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"for pkg in [\\\"lazypredict\\\",\\\"flaml\\\",\\\"kagglehub\\\",\\\"xgboost\\\",\\\"lightgbm\\\"]:\\n\", \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\", \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\n\", \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 9. Imports\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import os, warnings, glob\\n\", \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\\n\", \"from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\\n\", \"from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\\n\", \"from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score, f1_score, ConfusionMatrixDisplay, classification_report)\\n\", \"from lazypredict.Supervised import LazyClassifier\\n\", \"from flaml import AutoML\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\"); sns.set_theme(style=\\\"whitegrid\\\"); SEED=42\\n\", \"print(\\\"All imports loaded.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 10. Configuration / Constants\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"KAGGLE_SLUG = \\\"uciml/red-wine-quality-cortez-et-al-2009\\\"\\n\", \"TARGET = \\\"quality\\\"\\n\", \"TEST_SIZE = 0.15; VAL_SIZE = 0.15; SEED = 42; FLAML_BUDGET = 90\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Target: {TARGET}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 11. Dataset Download or Loading\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import kagglehub\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    path = kagglehub.dataset_download(KAGGLE_SLUG)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Downloaded to: {path}\\\")\\n\", \"except Exception as e:\\n\", \"    raise RuntimeError(f\\\"Download failed: {e}\\\")\\n\", \"csv_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(path,\\\"**\\\",\\\"*.csv\\\"), recursive=True)\\n\", \"df_raw = pd.read_csv(csv_files[0])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"df_raw.head()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 12. Data Validation Checks\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f\\\"Missing: {df_raw.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"df = df_raw.copy()\\n\", \"dupes = df.duplicated().sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Duplicates: {dupes}\\\")\\n\", \"if dupes > 0: df = df.drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"assert TARGET in df.columns\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nOriginal quality distribution:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts().sort_index()}\\\")\\n\", \"# Bin into 3 classes\\n\", \"def bin_quality(q):\\n\", \"    if q <= 5: return 0  # Low\\n\", \"    elif q == 6: return 1  # Medium\\n\", \"    else: return 2  # High\\n\", \"df[\\\"quality_class\\\"] = df[TARGET].apply(bin_quality)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nBinned distribution:\\\\n{df['quality_class'].value_counts().sort_index()}\\\")\\n\", \"TARGET = \\\"quality_class\\\"\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 13. Exploratory Data Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(12,4))\\n\", \"df[\\\"quality\\\"].value_counts().sort_index().plot.bar(ax=axes[0], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Original Quality Scores\\\")\\n\", \"df[TARGET].value_counts().sort_index().plot.bar(ax=axes[1], color=[\\\"coral\\\",\\\"gold\\\",\\\"forestgreen\\\"])\\n\", \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Binned Quality Classes\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_xticklabels([\\\"Low\\\",\\\"Medium\\\",\\\"High\\\"], rotation=0)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"num_feats = [c for c in df.columns if c not in [TARGET, \\\"quality\\\"]]\\n\", \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2,3, figsize=(15,8))\\n\", \"for ax, col in zip(axes.flat, [\\\"alcohol\\\",\\\"volatile acidity\\\",\\\"sulphates\\\",\\\"citric acid\\\",\\\"total sulfur dioxide\\\",\\\"pH\\\"]):\\n\", \"    if col in df.columns:\\n\", \"        for cls in sorted(df[TARGET].unique()):\\n\", \"            ax.hist(df[df[TARGET]==cls][col], bins=25, alpha=0.4, label=[\\\"Low\\\",\\\"Med\\\",\\\"High\\\"][cls])\\n\", \"        ax.set_title(col); ax.legend(fontsize=7)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"corr = df[num_feats + [TARGET]].corr()[TARGET].drop(TARGET).sort_values(key=abs, ascending=False)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Correlations with quality class:\\\")\\n\", \"print(corr)\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 14. Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Most wines are medium quality (score 6). Alcohol is the strongest predictor of quality.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(df[TARGET].value_counts(normalize=True).sort_index())\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 15. Train / Validation / Test Split\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"feat_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c not in [TARGET, \\\"quality\\\"]]\\n\", \"X = df[feat_cols]; y = df[TARGET]\\n\", \"X_tmp, X_test, y_tmp, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=y)\\n\", \"X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(X_tmp, y_tmp, test_size=VAL_SIZE/(1-TEST_SIZE), random_state=SEED, stratify=y_tmp)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Train: {X_train.shape}  Val: {X_val.shape}  Test: {X_test.shape}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 16. Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"All numeric features. StandardScaler for all.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"num_cols = X_train.columns.tolist()\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[\\n\", \"    (\\\"num\\\", StandardScaler(), num_cols)\\n\", \"], remainder=\\\"passthrough\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Numeric features: {len(num_cols)}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 17. Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- ACIDITY_RATIO: fixed acidity / volatile acidity\\n\", \"- SULFUR_RATIO: free sulfur dioxide / total sulfur dioxide\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"def eng(d):\\n\", \"    d = d.copy()\\n\", \"    if \\\"fixed acidity\\\" in d.columns and \\\"volatile acidity\\\" in d.columns:\\n\", \"        d[\\\"ACIDITY_RATIO\\\"] = d[\\\"fixed acidity\\\"] / d[\\\"volatile acidity\\\"].clip(lower=0.01)\\n\", \"    if \\\"free sulfur dioxide\\\" in d.columns and \\\"total sulfur dioxide\\\" in d.columns:\\n\", \"        d[\\\"SULFUR_RATIO\\\"] = d[\\\"free sulfur dioxide\\\"] / d[\\\"total sulfur dioxide\\\"].clip(lower=1)\\n\", \"    return d\\n\", \"X_train=eng(X_train); X_val=eng(X_val); X_test=eng(X_test)\\n\", \"num_cols = X_train.columns.tolist()\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[\\n\", \"    (\\\"num\\\", StandardScaler(), num_cols)\\n\", \"], remainder=\\\"passthrough\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Features: {X_train.shape[1]}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 18. Baseline Model\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"results = {}\\n\", \"for name, clf in [(\\\"Dummy\\\",DummyClassifier(strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\",random_state=SEED)),\\n\", \"                  (\\\"LogReg\\\",LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000,random_state=SEED)),\\n\", \"                  (\\\"RF\\\",RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1))]:\\n\", \"    pipe = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\",preprocessor),(\\\"clf\\\",clf)])\\n\", \"    pipe.fit(X_train, y_train); yp=pipe.predict(X_val)\\n\", \"    r={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_val,yp),\\\"Macro-F1\\\":f1_score(y_val,yp,average=\\\"macro\\\")}\\n\", \"    results[name]=r; print(f\\\"{name}: {r}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 19. LazyPredict Benchmark\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_lp=preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train); X_val_lp=preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"lazy=LazyClassifier(verbose=0,ignore_warnings=True,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"models_lp,_=lazy.fit(X_train_lp,X_val_lp,y_train,y_val)\\n\", \"models_lp.head(15)\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 20. FLAML AutoML Run\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"automl=AutoML()\\n\", \"automl.fit(X_train_lp,y_train,task=\\\"classification\\\",metric=\\\"macro_f1\\\",time_budget=FLAML_BUDGET,seed=SEED,verbose=0)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Best: {automl.best_estimator}\\\")\\n\", \"yp_fl=automl.predict(X_val_lp)\\n\", \"results[\\\"FLAML\\\"]={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_val,yp_fl),\\\"Macro-F1\\\":f1_score(y_val,yp_fl,average=\\\"macro\\\")}\\n\", \"print(results[\\\"FLAML\\\"])\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 21. Top 3 Model Selection\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"try:\\n\", \"    from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier; has_lgbm=True\\n\", \"except ImportError: has_lgbm=False\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    from xgboost import XGBClassifier; has_xgb=True\\n\", \"except ImportError: has_xgb=False\\n\", \"top3={}\\n\", \"if has_lgbm: top3[\\\"LightGBM\\\"]=LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=500,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=6,random_state=SEED,verbose=-1,n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"ExtraTrees\\\"]=ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=500,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"if has_xgb: top3[\\\"XGBoost\\\"]=XGBClassifier(n_estimators=500,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=6,random_state=SEED,verbosity=0,n_jobs=-1,eval_metric=\\\"mlogloss\\\")\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"AdaBoost\\\"]=AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=300,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"top3[\\\"GradBoosting\\\"]=GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=300,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=5,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Top 3: {list(top3.keys())}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 22. Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_tr_t=preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train); X_te_t=preprocessor.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"labels=[\\\"Low\\\",\\\"Medium\\\",\\\"High\\\"]\\n\", \"final={}\\n\", \"for name,mdl in top3.items():\\n\", \"    mdl.fit(X_tr_t,y_train); yp=mdl.predict(X_te_t)\\n\", \"    final[name]={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_test,yp),\\\"Macro-F1\\\":f1_score(y_test,yp,average=\\\"macro\\\")}\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{name}:\\\"); print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=labels))\\n\", \"pd.DataFrame(final).T\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,len(top3),figsize=(5*len(top3),4))\\n\", \"if len(top3)==1: axes=[axes]\\n\", \"for ax,(n,m) in zip(axes,top3.items()):\\n\", \"    ConfusionMatrixDisplay.from_predictions(y_test,m.predict(X_te_t),ax=ax,cmap=\\\"Blues\\\",display_labels=labels); ax.set_title(n)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 23. Error Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"bm=list(top3.values())[0]; ypb=bm.predict(X_te_t)\\n\", \"misclass = (y_test.values != ypb).sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Misclassified: {misclass}/{len(y_test)} ({misclass/len(y_test):.1%})\\\")\\n\", \"idx = np.where(y_test.values != ypb)[0]\\n\", \"if len(idx) > 0 and \\\"alcohol\\\" in X_test.columns:\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Mean alcohol (misclassified): {X_test.iloc[idx]['alcohol'].mean():.2f} vs overall: {X_test['alcohol'].mean():.2f}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 24. Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Alcohol content is the strongest quality predictor. Volatile acidity negatively correlates. Class boundaries are inherently fuzzy — sensory evaluation is subjective.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 25. Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Subjective quality scores (human tasters)\\n\", \"2. Only Portuguese Vinho Verde wines\\n\", \"3. Missing aroma/texture features\\n\", \"4. Ordinal binned to categorical\\n\", \"5. Small dataset (~1.6k red)\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 26. How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Combine red + white wine datasets\\n\", \"2. Ordinal regression\\n\", \"3. SMOTE for rare quality levels\\n\", \"4. Cross-validation\\n\", \"5. SHAP analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 27. Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Region-specific model\\n\", \"- Retrain with each vintage\\n\", \"- Supplement with sensory panel\\n\", \"- Price-quality calibration\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 28. Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Treating quality as regression (valid but different)\\n\", \"2. Not binning — too many thin classes\\n\", \"3. Ignoring class imbalance\\n\", \"4. Not noticing alcohol dominance\\n\", \"5. Assuming generalisability beyond Vinho Verde\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
